headline: Dow Retreats on Financials Weakness. Nasdaq Rises 0.3%.
summary: A heavy slide in financial stocks pushed the Dow lower on Friday, cementing a second consecutive weekly decline for the blue-chip index.  The Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 0.6%, or 274 points, on Friday.  The S&P 500 was flat while the Nasdaq Composite gained 0.3%.

headline: Capital One’s Brex Deal Is ‘Compelling.’ Why the Stock Is Falling Anyway.
summary: Capital One Financial  struck an agreement to acquire Brex, a fintech specializing in corporate credit cards, for nearly $5.2 billion.  The purchase price, consisting of a roughly 50/50 split between cash and stock, represents around 3.5% of Capital One’s market capitalization.  Jefferies analyst John Hecht noted that the acquisition supports Capital One’s aspirations in business payments.

headline: How Banks Can Appease Trump on Credit-Card Rates
summary: President Trump reiterated his desire for a credit-card interest rate cap this week.  Major card lenders  American Express Capital One Financial Citigroup JPMorgan Chase  and  Synchrony Financial  are all down this year.  Goldman Sachs  which has just exited a card business, has gained more than 8% so far this year.
